Follow @whyonthailand for more! ðThis is @jungle_doctorâs story about Mosha, an amputee elephant at the worldâs first hospital for elephants, the Friends of the Asian Elephant Foundation in Thailand.â£ ðð¹ð­

âMosha was only 7 months old when she arrived at the FAE and had lost her front leg to a landmine on Thailandâs border with Myanmar. She was attempting to compensate without the use of her limb by raising her trunk and leaning on other structures for support, but it was obvious that this would become increasingly difficult as she grew.â£

When looking for a solution to Moshaâs problem, there were a few things that needed to be taken into account. Firstly, Asian elephants can live well beyond 40 years in the wild, and Mosha was just at the start of her young life. Additionally, while euthanasia for such an injury may be considered as an option in many places around the world, in Thailand where a large percentage of the population follows Buddhism, it is not so readily discussed or practiced.

So, with assistance from orthopedic surgeon Doctor Jivacate, the team at the FAE decided to design and build a prosthetic leg to support Mosha throughout her life, with the first version of this leg weighing 15 kilograms and being made from a combination of plastic, sawdust, and metal.â£

Since that time, Mosha has received no fewer than ten prosthetic legs, the design adjusted and improved each time to support her needs as she grows. Today the prosthesis has evolved into a more sophisticated version of the first â as you can see here! â and is now constructed from an individual mold using thermoplastic, steel, and elastomer.â£â

In the quiet corners of a cozy home, a tiny ball of fur paces back and forth, its soft mewls echoing in the empty spaces. The warmth of the hearth no longer enough to quell the longing for the one who's gone. Every corner explored, every nook and cranny searched, but still, the absence persists. The kitten's whiskers twitch with anticipation, its eyes wide with hope, yearning for the familiar touch, the gentle caress that once brought solace and security. Memories dance in the air, the playful pounces, the shared moments of joy, now distant echoes in the vast expanse of solitude.

Outside, the world carries on, oblivious to the quiet plea of a tiny heart. But within these walls, the absence is palpable, a void that cannot be filled by the passing of time alone. Each passing moment feels like an eternity, each passing hour a reminder of the emptiness that lingers. Yet amidst the sorrow, there is a glimmer of hope, a beacon of light cutting through the darkness.

For even in the depths of despair, love endures. It is a bond that transcends distance and time, a thread that binds hearts together, even when separated by circumstance. And so, the kitten waits, its silent vigil a testament to the power of love, a silent declaration that no distance can diminish the connection between kindred souls.
